# Comparison SVG Template

## Overview

Template for side-by-side evaluations: versus layouts, feature matrices, pros/cons, and before/after comparisons.

---

## Base Structure

```svg
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1200 800" role="img">
  <title>[Comparison Title]</title>
  <desc>[Plain-text: comparison of A and B across N criteria]</desc>

  <style>
    :root {
      --accent: #E94560;
      --secondary: #16213E;
      --bg: #FFFFFF;
      --text: #333333;
      --muted: #888888;
      --positive: #2ECC71;
      --negative: #E74C3C;
      --neutral: #95A5A6;
      --light-bg: #F8F9FA;
      --font: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    }

    text { font-family: var(--font); }
    .title { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; fill: var(--secondary); }
    .subtitle { font-size: 16px; fill: var(--muted); }
    .option-name { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; }
    .criterion { font-size: 15px; fill: var(--text); }
    .detail { font-size: 13px; fill: var(--muted); }
    .source { font-size: 11px; fill: var(--muted); }
  </style>

  <rect width="1200" height="800" fill="var(--bg)" />

  <!-- Title -->
  <text x="600" y="50" class="title" text-anchor="middle">[Option A] vs [Option B]</text>
  <text x="600" y="78" class="subtitle" text-anchor="middle">[Context for the comparison]</text>

  <!-- Comparison content goes here -->

  <!-- Brand Logo -->
  <g transform="translate(1100, 740)" opacity="0.5">
    <!-- logo-mark -->
  </g>
</svg>
```

---

## Side-by-Side (Two Columns)

Classic A vs. B layout with a divider:

```svg
<!-- Left column header: Option A -->
<rect x="50" y="110" width="520" height="60" rx="8" fill="var(--accent)" />
<text x="310" y="148" class="option-name" text-anchor="middle" fill="white">[Option A]</text>

<!-- Right column header: Option B -->
<rect x="630" y="110" width="520" height="60" rx="8" fill="var(--secondary)" />
<text x="890" y="148" class="option-name" text-anchor="middle" fill="white">[Option B]</text>

<!-- Divider -->
<line x1="600" y1="110" x2="600" y2="720" stroke="var(--muted)" stroke-width="1"
      stroke-dasharray="4,4" />

<!-- Row 1 -->
<text x="310" y="220" class="criterion" text-anchor="middle">[A's value for criterion 1]</text>
<text x="600" y="205" class="detail" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">[Criterion 1]</text>
<text x="890" y="220" class="criterion" text-anchor="middle">[B's value for criterion 1]</text>
<line x1="80" y1="240" x2="1120" y2="240" stroke="var(--light-bg)" stroke-width="1" />

<!-- Row 2 -->
<text x="310" y="280" class="criterion" text-anchor="middle">[A's value for criterion 2]</text>
<text x="600" y="265" class="detail" text-anchor="middle" font-weight="600">[Criterion 2]</text>
<text x="890" y="280" class="criterion" text-anchor="middle">[B's value for criterion 2]</text>
<line x1="80" y1="300" x2="1120" y2="300" stroke="var(--light-bg)" stroke-width="1" />

<!-- Continue rows, spacing each ~60px apart -->
```

