## Pros and Cons

Two-column layout with positive/negative indicators:

```svg
<!-- Left: Pros -->
<rect x="50" y="110" width="520" height="60" rx="8" fill="var(--positive)" opacity="0.15" />
<text x="310" y="148" class="option-name" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--positive)">Pros</text>

<!-- Right: Cons -->
<rect x="630" y="110" width="520" height="60" rx="8" fill="var(--negative)" opacity="0.15" />
<text x="890" y="148" class="option-name" text-anchor="middle" fill="var(--negative)">Cons</text>

<!-- Pro item 1 -->
<g transform="translate(80, 200)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="8" fill="var(--positive)" />
  <text x="20" y="5" class="criterion">[Pro point 1]</text>
</g>

<!-- Pro item 2 -->
<g transform="translate(80, 250)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="8" fill="var(--positive)" />
  <text x="20" y="5" class="criterion">[Pro point 2]</text>
</g>

<!-- Con item 1 -->
<g transform="translate(660, 200)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="8" fill="var(--negative)" />
  <text x="20" y="5" class="criterion">[Con point 1]</text>
</g>

<!-- Con item 2 -->
<g transform="translate(660, 250)">
  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="8" fill="var(--negative)" />
  <text x="20" y="5" class="criterion">[Con point 2]</text>
</g>
```

