## Before/After

Split-screen showing transformation:

```svg
<!-- Before panel -->
<rect x="50" y="120" width="520" height="550" rx="12" fill="var(--light-bg)" />
<text x="310" y="160" class="option-name" text-anchor="middle"
      fill="var(--muted)">Before</text>
<!-- Before content: screenshot placeholder, description, or data -->
<rect x="80" y="190" width="460" height="260" rx="8" fill="white" stroke="var(--muted)"
      stroke-width="1" />
<text x="310" y="330" class="detail" text-anchor="middle">[Screenshot or illustration]</text>
<text x="310" y="500" class="criterion" text-anchor="middle">[Key metric before]</text>
<text x="310" y="530" class="detail" text-anchor="middle">[Context]</text>

<!-- Arrow between panels -->
<g transform="translate(585, 400)">
  <polygon points="0,-20 30,0 0,20" fill="var(--accent)" />
</g>

<!-- After panel -->
<rect x="630" y="120" width="520" height="550" rx="12" fill="var(--accent)" opacity="0.05" />
<text x="890" y="160" class="option-name" text-anchor="middle"
      fill="var(--accent)">After</text>
<rect x="660" y="190" width="460" height="260" rx="8" fill="white"
      stroke="var(--accent)" stroke-width="1" />
<text x="890" y="330" class="detail" text-anchor="middle">[Screenshot or illustration]</text>
<text x="890" y="500" class="criterion" text-anchor="middle"
      fill="var(--accent)">[Key metric after]</text>
<text x="890" y="530" class="detail" text-anchor="middle">[Context showing improvement]</text>
```

---

## Guidance

- Give equal visual weight to both sides unless the infographic is designed to argue for one option.
- Use color intentionally: accent for the recommended option, neutral for the other.
- Keep the same criteria in the same order on both sides.
- For feature matrices with more than 5 rows, group related features under sub-headers.
- For pros/cons, aim for balanced counts on each side (3-5 each). If one side dominates, the comparison feels rigged.
- Include a clear verdict or recommendation below the comparison if the purpose is to guide a decision.
